        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 5:10PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Blanche, or over Little River Canyon National
Preserve, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Weiss Dam, Leesburg, Cedar Bluff, Fullerton, New Moon, Yellow Creek
Falls, Cherokee Rock Village, Chesnut Bay Resort, Gaylesville,
Broomtown, Little River Canyon National Preserve, Cornwall Furnace
Park, Western Weiss Lake, Howells Crossroads, Blanche, Eastern Weiss
Lake, Sand Rock, Waterhouse, Chesterfield, and Little River Falls.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
